deck_excerpt: Noble Knight deck by YGO Lite
A standard Elemental HERO deck for multiple Fusion Summon
deck_description:
This is a deck I built for my friend, which is fairly simple to play. Combo #1: Keeper of Dragon Magic + 1 other card
  1. Normal Summon Keeper of Dragon Magic.
  2. Activate it's effect, discard the other card to add Neos Fusion.
  3. If one of the cards in your Graveyard is a Neo-Spacian monster or an Elemental HERO Neos, activate the 2nd effect of Keeper of Dragon Magic to Special Summon it in Defense Position.
  4. Activate Neos Fusion to Special Summon: Elemental HERO Brave Neos if you can destroy one of your opponent monsters to add Miracle Contact, or a Rainbow Neos for board clear. You can also Special Summon an Elemental HERO ... Neos for a specific purpose.
Combo #2: A Hero Lives + Neo Space Connector
  1. Activate A Hero Lives for Elemental HERO Prisma.
  2. Activate Prisma, send Elemental HERO Neos.
  3. Normal Summon Neo Space Connector.
  4. Activate Connector for a Neo-Spacian Aqua Dolphin or any Neo-Spacian monster.
  5. (Optional) Activate Aqua Dolphin.
  6. Tribute Neo Space Connector for Neos in the Graveyard.
  7. Either:
    • Link Summon Isolde, Two Tales of the Noble Knights to add Elemental HERO Stratos.
    • Contact Fusion to Elemental HERO Aqua Neos or any other Neos Fusion Monster you can.
Combo #3: A Hero Lives
  1. Activate A Hero Lives for Elemental HERO Stratos.
  2. Activate Elemental HERO Stratos for Elemental HERO Prisma.
  3. Normal Summon Prisma.
  4. Activate Elemental HERO Prisma, send Elemental HERO Neos.
  5. Link Summon to Isolde, Two Tales of the Noble Knights.
  6. Activate Isolde for Neo Space Connector for Turn 2.
That's all of the simple combos for this deck. This deck strategy will be updated soon.

deck_excerpt: The theater gets invaded by the odd eyes, while wild hope gets his butt spanked by electrumite and luster pendulum to generate plus
deck_description:
Abyss actor is one of my favorite decks of all time, though if I'm being honest, it isn't exactly the most consistent deck out there, especially when you play it pure. Maybe some of you have noticed too, but lots of the abyss actor monsters are a whole load of barnacles ( *cough* Leading lady *cough*). Though the combination out of abyss actor, luster pendulum and a small odd-eyes engine is a very consistent deck, that can bring out a few extra deck monsters and generates a butt-ton of plus with a few combos. like destroying wild hope with electrumite will give you a draw and a search on an abyss actor card. Or when your opening ceremony is destroyed ( Via the playhouse or a dumb opponent that doesn't know the effects of the script cards) while having a mellow madonna on the field.  To anyone who doesn't know the abyss actors, I will explain briefly how they work.

So almost all of the abyss actor monsters have in common that they work with the spells of the archetype, the abyss scripts. The abyss scripts all have two effects. One when they get activated and one when they get destroyed by an opponent's card effect. For example, the opening ceremony will give you 500 Lp when activated normally, but when its destroyed, you can draw cards until you have 5 in your hand. Most of the monsters will like I said, work with these cards. Superstar sets them directly from the deck and mellow madonna will special summon a level 4 or lower abyss actor from the deck when a script spell is activated.  This is like their main ,,startegy". Besides that, they are just a pendulum spam deck

I should mention that this is a pure budget deck, with the exception of one or two cards, the deck costs absolutely nothing. I've bought it for like 20 or 25 euros.  Though if you have some extra cash to spare, feel free to add a playset of ,,allure of darkness" as it is extra draw power.

I also want to thank anyone who clicked on this deck profile, I would have never imagined that so many people would read them, so thank you very very much for supporting me and leave a like if you want to

Summon Verre, Control the board, and play for card advantage.

You can survive a lot with just Verre on the board, but ideally you will want to get to a board with Verre, Haine, Summon Limit or Winda, and Magician's Right Hand with a copy of Golem Aruru in your hand.

The Deck is very vulnerable to handtraps but you can safely make plays if you draw Called by the Grave, or Instant fusion and use it to summon Millennium-Eyes Restrict.

If you summon Mellenium-Eyes, Thousand-Eyes, or El Shaddoll Winda you can bring it back using Witchcrafter Edal.

The deck is a bit slow so floodgates like summon limit and Winda hurt most opponents far more than it can hurt you.
don't banish macro cosmos with ragnarok eff and you win

Counter Fairy deck by YGO Lite
A Synchro deck with Resonators & Red Dragon Archfiend(I've still included a few more in there). This is a pure Synchro deck, no XYZ, Fusion, Pendulum,
deck_description:
I have the classic cards in this deck, Red Resonator, Synkron Resonator, Dark Resonator, etc. The main card in this Deck is the Red Resonator, but the most useful Synchro monster in this deck is going to be the Hot Red Dragon Archfiend Abyss, due to it's negate any effect on the field once per turn effect. So if possible, summon it first. Then after it attacks and IF you have Abyss and another monster you control, you can summon a tuner from the GY. If you have a level 1 tuner, Abyss, and any other monster you don't mind sending on a trip to the GY, summon Hot Red Dragon Archfiend Bane using Abyss as material, and using it's effect bring out Abyss again. Although you don't HAVE to follow this, in my opinion it's best to keep Abyss (without it's effect negated) on the field at all costs. This deck doesn't need much explanation to use (it's pretty simple to figure out if you read the monster effects), but I'll jot a few things down anyways.
  1. i) Red Resonator is probably the most useful tuner in this whole deck, and it;s all thanks to its' "Summon a lv.4 or lower monster from your hand when you normal summon this card" and "If Special summoned, once per turn, target a onster and gain LP equal to its' attack". If you have a Red Resonator and a lv.4 monster in your hand, summon Red Resonator, special summon (SS) the lv.4 monster, and Synchro summon Red Rising Dragon. Using Red Rising's effect, summon Red Resonator, gain LP equal to the highest monster on the field, then Synchro summon Scarlight Red Dragon Archfiend.ii) In case you Synchro summon Red Rising and have a level 3 tuner in the GY, SS that and Synchro summon Hot Red Dragon Archfiend Abyss. iii) This third case is possible only when you can somehow summon a level 1 tuner on the field even after summoning Red Resonator (Using Double Summon or the Synkron Resonator on your hand, or if your opponent has a monster from his extra deck on the field and you have a Mirror Resonator). Synchro summon Scarlight, remove any monster on the opponents' field which can be by Scarlights' effect, then Synchro summon Abyss.
  2. I've added some level 5 and level 7 synchro's for a reason, in the case you don't have the above case possible. If the opponent uses a lot of effects to rid the monsters on your field, Synchro summon Clear Wing Synchro Dragon to negate one on you (and also gain attack!). If somehow you still have Clear Wing on the field and get a level 1 dark tuner, summon Beelze or  Odd-Eyes Wing Dragon (judge the situation wisely).
  3. I've added  Tyrant Red Dragon Archfiend in this deck for purely one reason, to git rid of all the annoying cards the opponent has on the field. The good thing about Tyrant is that you don't need any specific monster archetype or any specific attributed tuner to bring it out, if you have 2 level 3 tuners and a level 4 monster, you can bring this out. If you have a Red Rising on the field and somehow 2 level 2 tuners, bring him out. Thanks to this freedom of choice you have you can out this card in any other deck for a Synchro backup. The only downside is that you need two tuners for it, which also isn't hard if Hot Red Dragon Archfiend Bane attacks and deals damage (it can summon two tuners of the same level, one from the GY, and the other from your deck).
  4. I added Schwarzchild Limit Dragon just because I could, my original plan was to summon a Scarlight and then this dragon to XYZ summon a Galaxy Eyes Cipher Dragon and then a Galaxy Eyes Cipher Blade or Full Armour, but I decided to ditch  that plan last moment, so do as you wish.
  5. Red Sprinter is pretty useful when the field is empty, because if you don't have a red resonator yet and have some other tuner in your hand or GY (or just have Red Resonator in your GY), you can SS it and Synchro.
  6. King's Consonance is really useful in case your field is empty and you have monsters in your GY, so is King's synchro but you'll need a Synchro monster getting attacked for King's Synchro to be useful.
Any suggestions and new combos or such will be appreciated, leave em' in the comments and I'll check them out!

deck_excerpt: A code talker deck who s goal is to extra link turn 1 with only 2 cards.

deck_description:
This deck is just two META deck, facing each other (Salamangreat and Orcust). In one match, you can change your playstyle to the other deck.

Strategy:

As I said, you are playing META. But it's harder because you will have 25 support card in your main deck, and the other 15 card is Salamangreat card. Then if I have 25 side deck card in my main deck, what is in my side deck? I hear you ask, The answer is simple. If you look a the first paragraph I write. And I didn't mention it yet, so your side deck will full of 15 Orcust cards. But don't worry, we divide extra deck space so you can put both Salamangreat and Orcusts' Extra deck monsters in 1 Extra deck, so you will have much space for your side deck for Orcust. We also give you 3 Pot of extravagance in your deck.

In conclusion:

 

Don't play this deck in a single game. Play only on the match game.

This Deck is the combination of 4 META deck at the moment (Danger! Orcust Salamangreat and burn) So, Salamangreat Won 4 out of 5 WCQ, If you have all these decks combined and use it in WCQ, You can win 1st place in all 20 WCQ out of 5 WCQ and get first place on every tournaments.

Strategy:

This deck has similar strategy compare to those 4 META deck. If you have a lot of Orcust card in your hand, play like what Orcust player usually do. If you start with 3 Salamangreat cards on your hand, play Salamangreat.

So, the conclusion is

The only combos this deck can pull of is Orcust or Salamangreat. The Danger! just help you send the card you want to be in GY to GY. and burn is just a joke here.

My new D/D/D deck utilizing G.O.D.
deck_description: The new and improved version of my D/D/D deck. This deck utilizes the new boss monster from the manga Divine Go-D/D/D zero king G.O.D Reiji. This card is quite useful as a scale not only having a pendulum scale of 0 but the effect to normal summon any level 5 or higher D/D/D monster from your hand. D/D savant Copernicus This card is the decks' main combo starter and is extremely flexible. If you draw this card on your first turn and one other D/D card you can combo into either a zefra metaltron or a D/D/D abyss king gilgamesh. The first combo ends with D/D/D abyss king gilgamesh a full scale and the D/D savant copernicus on the field. Start by normal summoning D/D savant copernicus and use its effect to send D/D swirl slime to the graveyard then banish it and special summon any D/D monster from your hand. Use both D/D monsters on the field to go into D/D/D abyss king gilgamesh and activate his effect to set a pendulum scale. I usually use D/D/D destiny king zero larplace and D/D savant newton. You can then pendulum summon the D/D savant copernicus back from the extra deck as well as any other D/D monsters in your hand.  The second combo requires you to start with D/D savant copernicus and one other D/D monster or dark contract in hand. Normal summon D/D savant copernicusand send D/D lamia to the graveyard. Then use D/D lamia's effect to special summon itself from the graveyard. Using both monsters go into crystron needlefiber using his effect special summon a second copy of D/D lamia from your deck. Using this D/D lamia go into Linkuriboh, then using both crystron needlefiber and Linkuriboh as materials special summon zefra metaltron. D/D swirl slime D/D swirl slime is one of the best combo starters in the deck as it gets you two monsters on the field for the cost of two monsters in hand. Usually, when you start with swirl slime you fusion summon straight into D/D/D flame king genghis or D/D/D flame king high genghis and then special summon another monster straight out of your hand. This card is usually the target for cards like foolish burial and D/D savant copernicus because it can special summon any D/D monster from your hand. D/D/D abyss king gilgamesh I usually try to make this card on my first turn to set my pendulum scales with D/D savant newton and either Divine Go-D/D/D zero king G.O.D Reiji or D/D/D oblivion king abyss ragnarok. After this the card kind of just sits there the best thing to do after you summon D/D/D abyss king gilgamesh is let your opponent destroy it this lets you special summon a D/D monster from your extra deck or graveyard in defence position ignoring it's summoning conditions. I usually special summon D/D/D super doom king bright armageddon off of this effect as it stops your opponent from being able to disassemble your board with it's protection effect also it's high stat line usually means your opponent won't be able to destroy it by battle.

deck_excerpt: weak to all interuption , but a fun deck to be creative with . lots of different mini combos with each hand
deck_description:
this is not a meta deck by any measure , but it is really fun to play and i usually hate combo decks . it has lots of smaller less meta combos so youll never be seeing 5 negates on turn 1 , but ive found it to be pretty consistent and able to combo off in many different ways . can OTK with optimal conditions or can stall a little too

contains:

-world chalice core to get things going

-world legacy support cards and dark machine types

-small orcust engine to help either draw into combo pieces or provide a negate

-mini guardragon engine to summon brotaur , search chaos dragon , summon CDL + destroy 2 , link borrelsword

-ability to use monstrosity and knightmare cards to get true king of calamities or world gears , providing a floodgate or a field nuke if resoloved

deck_name: Galaxy Photon July 2019 Meta - Post Battle of Legends
deck_excerpt: All the stars have aligned and reign is about to be unleashed with the addition of Draglubion. All strategies explained
deck_description:
Just you usual Galaxy Photon deck with  tonne's of handtraps and a spice of Number 97: Draglubion, maybe this is the card Galaxy always needed. (If you're having troubles using Number 97: Draglubion in YgoPro2 TCG matches , that's the fault of the client. This card is completely TCG legal and is being used in tournaments so download some other client that's frequently updated like YGOPRO percy.) Some tips:
  1. This deck has the potential of an FTK/OTK depends on your hand , if you are successfully able to summon Galaxy-Eyes Sol Flare Dragon and Number 97: Draglubion on your going first DO NOT summon Number C107: Neo Galaxy-Eyes Tachyon Dragon with the effect of Draglubion because it can instantly get Kaijued, summon something like Number 38: Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy.
  2. For OTK same combo with Sol Flare and Draglubion but this time you summon Number 100: Numeron Dragon that can boost its ATK to insane amounts.
  3. For board lock down same combo with Sol Flare and Draglubion but this time you summon C107 and activate its effect to negate all effects of all face up cards and also no effects can be activated during that turn.
Note - You can experiment with all possible combos whichever suits your play style but the basic board should be Sol Flare + Draglubion, may wary on the situation you're currently in. For any further queries drop a comment. If this deck works for you consider supporting me on Paypal - A coffee

deck_name: Character Deck: Dinosaur Ryuzaki / Rex Raptor
deck_excerpt: A fun deck designed for Dinosaur Ryuzaki, the brute-force master of dinosaur beatdown! Designed to be faithful in theme and strategy to the character'
deck_description:
Art Credit: FoolishLittleMortal

Deck Themes: Dinosaurs, high ATK, high-level summons, "Black" dinosaur series Aesthetic: Pure dinosaur designs, wild prehistoric Earth, minimal influence from more modern or comedic tones. Strategy: Summon high-ATK dinosaurs and buff them up with support cards, and hit the opponent hard. There are many cards to help cheat out the higher level Dinosaur monsters, and a smattering of high-level Dragons to bring the pain on the field. Destruction effects are minimal, with almost zero anti-S/T elements to the deck. Card Choices: 
  • Black Ptera: Acts to replace the anime-only Kaitoptera, so it has multiple copies instead of the single copy that the other Black dinos get.
  • Black dinosaurs: A unique series/sub-theme not used by any other existing characters, this sort of non-archetype series of related monsters feels very true to early Yu-Gi-Oh!
  • Jurassic World: A simple ATK boost for Dinosaurs, this card is ultra-basic and very true to early-era Duel Monsters. Although it and Destroyersaurus were used by Tyranno Kenzan in GX, I feel this is generic and basic enough of a card, and aesthetically perfect, to justify use in this deck. However, due to the connections to Tyranno, it is likely this will end up subbed out for the "Dinosaur Kingdom" Field Spell from the upcoming Ultimate Predators starter deck that is themed around Rex Raptor and Weevil Underwood.
  • The Earth - Hex-Sealed Fusion & Instant Fusion: Acts as a way to summon out the lower level Dinosaur Fusion monsters that Ryuzaki already has half of the fusion materials for. In the case of Instant Fusion, it can also provide handy tribute fodder for a Tribute Summon.
  • Razor Lizard: Although comical and not quite fitting the naturalistic aesthetics of most of Ryuzaki's deck, this card fits vaguely with Balloon Lizard as a goofy-but-not-too-cartoonish Reptile and existed back in the DM era. The only other real option in non-archetyped Reptiles was Don Turtle, and since turtles don't have a strong relationship to dinosaurs in public perception I passed on choosing it.
Exclusions: Though there are many more strong high-level dinosaurs that could be options, many of them were excluded due to being used by or associated with Tyranno Kenzan in the GX anime. This includes Ultimate Tyranno, Super Conductor Tyranno, Ultimate Conductor Tyranno, Tyranno Infinity and Saurobeast Brachio. Design Intent: Casual. All character decks I design are intended to play against each other and are tweaked to do so, being 50 cards and having a side deck as well. Generally a balance between consistency and authenticity is intended, so while multiple copies of cards may be run the idea is to see a wide variety of plays, much like in the anime/manga.

deck_excerpt: X-Saber Deck: classic build + link format
deck_description:
Same old classic strategy, consisting Faultroll and Boggart Knight quick spam + Gottom's Emegency Call for mid game. Just added a little spice with the help of Rescue Cat, Crystron Needlefiber and Missus Radiant (soon to add I:P Maskerena).

Rescue Cat + Faultroll opening will bring out Darksoul and Airbellum to Needlefiber. Then +2 monsters from Faultroll and Needlefiber for synchro summon of your choice, depends on opponent's deck. (Can open powerful synchro level 6 or level 5, i.e. Naturia Beast or Barkion)

Same strategy with Boggart Knight + Faultroll and additional X-Saber tuner monster. If you only have Rescue Cat on your first turn, you can abuse double search from Darksoul. (bring out 2 Darksouls from Rescue Cat then link summon Missus Radiant, then search 2 essential X-Saber at end phase)

Main 3 Called by the Grave for protection from hand traps, and 3 Red Reboot for continuous combo + Hyunlei's clean up of S/T card.

Deck build will be updated timely.
Pretty basic, try to get out my strongest LV cards with a nice backup from Slifer.
